"SECTION 12. IC 35-46-3-15, AS AMENDED BY P.L.141-2019,
SECTION 11, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 15. (a) This section does not apply to the
following:
(1) A state or federally inspected livestock slaughtering facility
(for conduct authorized by IC 15-17-5 and rules adopted under
EH 1165—LS 6739/DI 150

21
that chapter).
(2) An animal disease diagnostic laboratory established under
IC 21-46-3-1.
(3) A postsecondary educational institution.
(4) A research facility licensed by the United States Department
of Agriculture.
(b) As used in this section, "animal" has the meaning set forth in
IC 35-46-3-3. section 3 of this chapter.
(c) A person, including a humane society, an animal control
agency, or a governmental entity operating an animal shelter or
other animal impounding facility, who knowingly or intentionally
destroys or authorizes the destruction of an animal by:
(1) placing the animal in a decompression chamber and lowering
